{
  "texts": [
    "I already mentioned your first question in my statement, and you summarized it well.",
    "I think the goal of quality education reform is to solve the problem of focusing only on students' academic performance and ignoring their problem-solving and other abilities.",
    "Although academic performance can reflect some of students' abilities, it cannot be the only pursuit of students.",
    "Traditional cramming teaching is difficult to cultivate students' practical abilities, communication skills, teamwork skills, critical thinking, etc.",
    "But these abilities are essential as they enter college and later when they face more of the tasks of study and work alone."
  ]
}